 HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uroseannelottsa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roseanne Lottsa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Skald TL</span><br>  Posts: 193<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/12/02 7:45:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> In Depth discussion</span><hr size=1> I would like to put together a single document decribing why the Skald class is fun.  Let's work on it together.<br><br>The thing is, I do not want to list the Skald's abilities as being fun (ie speed, damage shouts, etc)  I want to come up with a  document that goes deeper and explains in a non-specific class way what the 'fun' actually is.  Is is mobility that makes it fun?  Is it good lower level PvE power?  Is it the ability to survive being jumped?<br><br>That is the kind of thing I want.  If we can get to the nitty gritty of what makes the Skald fun, then maybe this document we produce can be used to help the other classes who are not 'fun' to play.<br><br>I hope that made sense.<br><br>Rosey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uclapperoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/12/02 8:35:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In Depth discussion</span><hr size=1> Nice idea.  How's this:<br><br>Variety is the spice of skalds:<br><br>When choosing a class, a player decides what kind of game they want to play, primarily under the three categories of melee, caster and support.  <br><br>Why decide?  Do a little bit of all of the above, and do most of them pretty well.  People say skalds can't tank, but we hold our own.  People think skalds don't count as casters, but see how long a skald holds out before asking for purity.  People think of support classes in terms of healing, but just wait for a zerker to ask for damage add.<br><br>The fun is in the ability to twist and choose a variety of abilities effectively.  In large groups I'm a two gun kid blasting away with my DDs whenever I can, mixing it up with my fists and sword in between.  Soloing I'm balancing survival vs. hunting with my mez and snare abilities.  With a small group I'm staying in the heart of things adding all of my abilities where needed.<br><br>People call us a &quot;hybrid&quot; but I call us the total jacks of all trades (and masters of...some).  Simplicity becomes stale, complexity brings...adventure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uaaliainsidiae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalia Insidiae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/18/02 9:08:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skalds as a 'fun' class.</span><hr size=1> I'll admit, when I first made my skald, it was in order to provide two things to my group.  Tanking and speed.  As I have progressed and eventually gotten to level 50, that has changed and my reasons for enjoying my class are far beyond any single ability.  I am a shield/one hand axe skald primarily, only using a 2 hander against mean paladins with their blasted heal chant.<br><br>From a PVE standpoint, I am able to perform a multiple of roles ranging from MA against some pretty mean mobs, peeler for my poor healers that get beat on, damage, and moral support for the group to keep their spirits up.<br><br>From an RVR standpoint, there is nothing truly more satisfying than setting your target on a particular person (usually a cleric or bard), charging in while your group assaults the horde, and taking out that key person with a combination of all of our abilities, while at the same time still supporting the group with either speed, damage add, or even regen.<br><br>And really.  What other class gets the benefit of beating up on people, shouting at them like mad, making them slow, running around faster than most anyone else, and above all, gets to tell the stupidest stories and write the silliest poem, all the in the name of their realm?<br><br><br> <p>Qira Faerethorn<br>Suicide Skald of Merlin<br>Guildmistress of Blood Raven</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uharleybrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HarleyBrown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/19/02 6:06:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skalds as a 'fun' class.</span><hr size=1> A little history on my behalf.<br><br>I started playing DAOC about 6 months ago.  My first character was a blademaster in Hibernia, but after 6 levels I bored of that and tried a paladin in Albion.  Again, after 7 levels, I learnt that paladins were not effective in RvR, and dumped that one as well.  I didn't learn my lesson however, and after starting a Norseman Viking, I witnessed a berserker morphing into a 'bear' (aka rat) and thought wow, so I submitted to Modi and started a berserker.  I levelled my beloved berserker for 35 levels but it was at that stage I really learnt how gimped the class was in RvR.  After being mezzed and stunned and used as a pin cushion, I was impressed with the quality of information around for hunters (Information from the hunter Team leader and other websites such as Namuna's was invaluable) and started a Kobold hunter.  I loved that little guy, but I still wasnt satisfied.  So after 22 levels with hunter, I rerolled yet again, and strived to be a skald.<br><br>Well, let me say, this is the class for me.  I just wish I had of found this class before any of the others, but learning processes are always important.<br><br>For the first time I rolled a Troll.  I love their size, their kick-ass appearance, their bellow and grunt when they get hit.  To me they define Midgard in that no other realm really has anything that compares to the daunting size and looks of a troll.<br><br>After hitting level 5-10 and increasing Battlesongs I finally understood class satisfaction.  Being able to use not only 1 but 2 direct damage spells as well as clobbering the hell out of my opponent with my hammer was pure bliss.  It was great, but I was totally unprepared with the joy that being able to run everywhere at a far greater speed than anyone else would generate.  Kill tasks up to level 20 were an absolute breeze as the effort in getting somewhere was so easy.  <br><br>Being able to snare my target from a field of aggressive opponents and bring them slowly but surely to my hammer was sensational.  My groups loved me for my speed, for my damage add songs, and also for my assistance in faster healing during the restful times.  I am more than mere group assistance however, and many times I have been used for my tanking abilities.<br><br>I am effective in PvE situations and also in RvR.  In my mind, most group would be crazy not to want a skald in the midst.<br><br>Long live the skald! <p>Bragge Tunecrusher (Skald) <BR>Gunreth Doublebarrel (Berserker) <BR>Yelrah Mingunr (Hunter) <BR>Knights of Ni on Kay<BR>-------------------------------<BR>Ever dance with the devil in the moonlight?</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=182.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=182.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=182.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=182.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=182.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cell